			"after": " The first successful use of poison gas as a weapon of warfare occurred during the Second Battle of Ypres April 22 May 25 1915 248 Gas was soon used by all major belligerents throughout the war It is estimated that the use of chemical weapons employed by both sides throughout the war had inflicted 1 3 million casualties For example the British had over 180 000 chemical weapons casualties during the war and up to one third of American casualties were caused by them The Russian Army reportedly suffered roughly 500 000 chemical weapon casualties in World War I 249 The use of chemical weapons in warfare was in direct violation of the 1899 Hague Declaration Concerning Asphyxiating Gases and the 1907 Hague Convention on Land Warfare which prohibited their use 250 251 ",
